    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="881"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d881">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.93114A/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-28">September 28,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received September 28—10:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6041. American interests, Hong Kong. Department’s 1230, May 22;<note n="82"
                        xml:id="d881fn82">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1023">p. 1023</ref>.</note>
                    Legation’s 4353, July 22.<note n="83" xml:id="d881fn83">Not printed; it reported
                        that the contents of telegram No. 1602, July 6, to the Minister in
                        Switzerland had been communicated to the Japanese Foreign Office on July 16
                        (740.00114A Pacific War/553).</note> Swiss note September 23 states
                    following <pb facs="1015" n="1003" xml:id="pg_1003"/> substance reply Japanese
                    Foreign Office to Swiss Legation Tokyo pursuant latter’s representations
                    protection American interests Hong Kong.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>Japanese Government does not yet envisage possibility modification its
                        decision not authorize representation by third power of interests enemy
                        country in territories occupied Japanese forces. It permits however to such
                        extent possible dispatch monetary relief and in kind to POWs and civilian
                        internees detained such territories.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
